<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Cloud on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/cloud/</link><description>Recent content in Cloud on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/cloud/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] iCloud Sync Conflict Error on Mac</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-icloud-error-v2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-icloud-error-v2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="icloud-sync-conflict-error-on-mac"&gt;iCloud Sync Conflict Error on Mac&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;iCloud shows sync conflicts, documents don&amp;rsquo;t update across devices, or &amp;ldquo;conflict&amp;rdquo; copies appear in Finder.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;iCloud sync conflicts occur when the same document is edited on multiple devices simultaneously, or when sync fails due to network issues, storage limits, or account problems. Conflicting versions are saved as separate files.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Same document edited offline on multiple devices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Network connectivity during sync&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;iCloud storage full&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;iCloud account signed out on one device&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Third-party apps not iCloud-aware&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Date/time mismatch between devices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="check-icloud-storage"&gt;Check iCloud Storage&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check iCloud storage usage&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;du -sh ~/Library/Mobile&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\ &lt;/span&gt;Documents/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Or via System Settings &amp;gt; Apple ID &amp;gt; iCloud&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Free up space if near limit&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="resolve-conflicts-manually"&gt;Resolve Conflicts Manually&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Find conflict files&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;find ~/Library/Mobile&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\ &lt;/span&gt;Documents -name &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;*conflict*&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Conflict files are usually named:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# DocumentName (Conflicted copy date).ext&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Compare and merge manually&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="force-icloud-sync"&gt;Force iCloud Sync&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Reset iCloud sync daemon&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;killall bird
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Reset iCloud Drive sync&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;brctl log --wait --shorten 2&amp;gt;&amp;amp;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; | head -100
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Monitor sync activity&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;brctl status
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-account-status"&gt;Check Account Status&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Verify iCloud sign-in&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;defaults read MobileMeAccounts 2&amp;gt;/dev/null | grep -A &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt; AccountID
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Sign out and back in if needed&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# System Settings &amp;gt; Apple ID &amp;gt; Sign Out (keep data)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Then sign back in&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="clear-icloud-cache"&gt;Clear iCloud Cache&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Reset iCloud document cache&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;rm -rf ~/Library/Caches/CloudKit/*
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Reset iCloud Drive cache&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;rm -rf ~/Library/Mobile&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\ &lt;/span&gt;Documents/.DS_Store
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-date-and-time"&gt;Check Date and Time&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Sync conflicts can occur with time mismatches&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo systemsetup -setusingnetworktime on
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo sntp -sS time.apple.com
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-apple-id-error-v2/"&gt;Apple ID Error&lt;/a&gt; — Account issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-timemachine-error-v2/"&gt;Time Machine Error&lt;/a&gt; — Backup issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-wifi-error-v2/"&gt;Wi-Fi Error&lt;/a&gt; — Network issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Linux terraform Provider Error — Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/linux-terraform-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/linux-terraform-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="linux-terraform-provider-error"&gt;Linux: terraform: provider error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;terraform: provider error&lt;/code&gt; message means Terraform encountered a problem installing, initializing, or communicating with a provider. Providers are plugins that interact with cloud platforms, SaaS providers, and other APIs. Provider errors prevent Terraform from planning or applying infrastructure changes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Terraform providers are separate binaries downloaded from the Terraform Registry or other sources. When a provider fails, Terraform cannot interact with the target API. Common errors include &lt;code&gt;Failed to install provider&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;Error: Failed to instantiate provider&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;provider configuration not present&lt;/code&gt;. These indicate download failures, authentication issues, or compatibility problems.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] macOS iCloud Sync Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-icloud-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-icloud-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="macos-icloud-sync-error-fix"&gt;macOS iCloud Sync Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;iCloud sync errors occur when your Mac fails to synchronize data with iCloud. You may see &amp;ldquo;Unable to sync,&amp;rdquo; spinning indicators next to iCloud apps, or data not appearing on other devices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;iCloud sync relies on a persistent connection to Apple&amp;rsquo;s servers. Sync failures are typically caused by network issues, authentication token expiration, or corrupt local sync databases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Network connectivity issues blocking iCloud servers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expired or corrupted iCloud authentication token&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insufficient local storage for iCloud Drive&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;iCloud server outages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Date/time settings preventing SSL authentication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Third-party security software blocking iCloud connections&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-sign-out-and-sign-back-into-icloud"&gt;1. Sign out and sign back into iCloud&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# System Preferences → Apple ID → Overview → Sign Out&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Choose to keep a copy of iCloud data on this Mac&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wait for sign-out to complete&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Sign back in with your Apple ID&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-reset-icloud-sync-database"&gt;2. Reset iCloud sync database&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Stop iCloud services&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;launchctl unload -w /System/Library/LaunchDaemons/com.apple.cloudd.plist
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Delete the sync database&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;rm -rf ~/Library/Application&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\ &lt;/span&gt;Support/CloudDocs/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Restart iCloud services&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;launchctl load -w /System/Library/LaunchDaemons/com.apple.cloudd.plist
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="3-check-icloud-system-status"&gt;3. Check iCloud system status&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Open System Preferences → Apple ID → iCloud&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check which services are enabled&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Visit https://www.apple.com/support/systemstatus/ for server status&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="4-force-icloud-reindex"&gt;4. Force iCloud reindex&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Reindex iCloud Drive&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mdutil -E /System/Volumes/Data/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check indexing status&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mdutil -s /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="cloudkit-error"&gt;CloudKit Error&lt;/a&gt; — CloudKit framework sync errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="macos-apple-id-error"&gt;Apple ID Error&lt;/a&gt; — Apple ID authentication failures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="nsurlerror"&gt;Network Errors&lt;/a&gt; — general network connectivity issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] macOS iCloud Sync Error — Couldn't Connect to iCloud</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/icloud-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/icloud-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="icloud-sync-error--couldnt-connect-to-icloud"&gt;iCloud Sync Error — Couldn&amp;rsquo;t Connect to iCloud&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An iCloud sync error occurs when your Mac cannot communicate with Apple&amp;rsquo;s iCloud servers or the sync process fails silently. You may see &amp;ldquo;Couldn&amp;rsquo;t connect to iCloud,&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;Syncing paused,&amp;rdquo; or data that doesn&amp;rsquo;t appear on your other devices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;iCloud synchronization depends on network connectivity, Apple ID authentication, sufficient storage, and a functioning sync daemon. When any of these fail, syncing stops and you may see error dialogs or stale data.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Expo - EAS build error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/frameworks/react-native/rn-expo-build-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/frameworks/react-native/rn-expo-build-error/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;An EAS build error occurs when Expo Application Services fails to build your app in the cloud. This can happen during the Android or iOS build phase due to configuration issues, dependency problems, or platform-specific errors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing or invalid &lt;code&gt;eas.json&lt;/code&gt; configuration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build profile does not match project requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Native dependencies incompatible with EAS build environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing environment variables or secrets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;App version/build number conflicts on iOS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify &lt;code&gt;eas.json&lt;/code&gt; configuration:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-json" data-lang="json"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;{
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;#34;build&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;#34;development&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;#34;developmentClient&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;,
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;#34;distribution&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;internal&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; },
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;#34;preview&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;#34;distribution&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;internal&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; },
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;#34;production&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: {}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start="2"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Check build logs for specific errors:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;eas build:list
